==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Swans-down
<hw>Swans"-down`</hw> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The down,
or fine, soft feathers, of the swan, used on various articles of
dress.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A fine, soft, thick cloth of wool mixed with silk or
cotton; a sort of twilled fustian, like moleskin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Swan's-down cotton</b></col>. <cd>See <cref>Cotton
flannel</cref>, under <er>Cotton</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swanskin</ent>⟦br⟧
